{
  "stem": "10181.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "But in the end, they were thrown out and had Russian prisoners of war working there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "And they were sort of surprised to see kids, you know, right across the road from them in a-- they'd never seen that before, kids in a concentration camp, you know.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "There was a Russian prisoner-of-war camp not far away in Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "So one or-- once or twice, I-- I managed to crawl out through the barbed wire at night to the kitchen, and they gave me some-- some stale bread, you know, which was very dangerous, I think, for them and-- [INAUDIBLE] for me, of course, but for them also.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "You know, they weren't allowed to-- not supposed to do that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "And this is really what we did.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 76,
      "text": "We tried to sort of find ways and means to-- to-- to survive.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then, like I said, it was a blur.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't really-- can't tell you anything particular of-- of that time period, just a lot of people dying, and dying, you know, just being left there or dying in the barracks or dying in their beds.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I-- what I remember is that at one time, March, April, we started hearing guns in the distance, OK, which according to the German guards were British, OK?",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Those few who came to the camp told us these were British.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But it wasn't over for us because in the beginning of April, they decided to evacuate our camp for whatever reason and put it on a train.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we were called, and we were put on the train in the first week in April, I think it was.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we had to walk.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This time there were no trucks to take us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had to walk all the way to Celle, which was very difficult because all those were sick.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we had this-- aside from some-- some of us having typhus, we had this-- you get this disease from hunger.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was called edema or something like that, but-- the-- the way your-- everything swells, you know-- your-- your your legs swell, and-- and your-- you know, your joints swell up, and-- and this is-- this comes from-- from malnutrition, from hunger.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we walked to the-- to the train.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And this is one-- one of the few-- I saw-- we were guarded by German soldiers.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I think they were soldiers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I don't think they were SS.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I'm not sure.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But one or two of the soldiers tried to help some of the smaller children-- because there were children and-- and-- and-- to-- to make it.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was one of those cattle wagons where we got on.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we were I don't know how many in a cattle wagon.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It was-- the door was closed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we traveled like that for about five days.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We stopped once or twice in the middle.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But once we were let out and once we went and once we-- we were at a town called Stendal, which was-- in-- and in the railroad station and was being bombed.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they moved us out just as we were being bombed.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that-- after five days-- five or six days-- the train finally stopped near the Elbe.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was near the Elbe, which I didn't know it at the time, but I know it was near Magdeburg.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was a little town, or a little village, called Hillersleben nearby.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Next to the wagon, the-- the-- the-- the cattle wagon where I was were the German guards behind us.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They had, like, a regular-- regular railroad car where they lived, and they had lots of food, at least lots of bread.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was looking for bread.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Bread was the main thing which interested me by that time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And when we stopped, we were allowed-- we were allowed to get off the train.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And all those years, I never spoke German.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I didn't want to.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Even if I understood and I-- I spoke, I didn't want to speak German.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I spoke Dutch.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Then I asked one of the German guards what-- what was happening.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he said, well, the engine went away to see-- there apparently is a-- a German-- not a German, an-- an American unit in the area.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they went to see what's happening, you know, and if the engine doesn't come back-- back by nightfall, that means the-- the Americans are coming, and they're going to leave.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then in afternoon, they had some-- they gave us-- those who were close by, they gave us some of the bread they had.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They gave it to us, and they left.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And then I started to walk to the village, and I knocked on the door.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There-- there was nobody outside.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I knocked on the doors and asked for food.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
